title: Lord Nelson's Flagship, the Foudroyant
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: Rectangular, with lobed top, bottom, and sides, featuring raised decoration of a large sail boat with 3 masts in central, rectangular reserve, inscribed "'Foudroyant', Nelson's Flagship, Commenced 1789, Launched 1789, Wrecked Blackpool 1897", incised decorative surround, reverse features incised decoration.
